modules.name: Data.Set
modules.comments:
This module defines a type of sets as balanced 2-3 trees, based on
<http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~dpw/courses/cos326-12/ass/2-3-trees.pdf>

Qualified import is encouraged, so as to avoid name clashes with other modules.

declarations.comments: `Set a` represents a set of values of type `a`
declarations.title: Set

declarations.comments: Test if a set is empty
declarations.title: isEmpty

declarations.comments: Create a set with one element
declarations.title: singleton

declarations.comments:
Check whether the underlying tree satisfies the 2-3 invariant

This function is provided for internal use.
declarations.title: checkValid

declarations.comments: Test if a value is a member of a set
declarations.title: member

declarations.comments: Insert a value into a set
declarations.title: insert

declarations.comments: Delete a value from a set
declarations.title: delete

declarations.comments: Convert a set to a list
declarations.title: toList

declarations.comments: Create a set from a list of elements
declarations.title: fromList

declarations.comments: Find the size of a set
declarations.title: size

declarations.comments:
Form the union of two sets

Running time: `O(n * log(m))`
declarations.title: union

declarations.comments: Form the union of a collection of sets
declarations.title: unions
